input_str: Standing alongside an array of American flags in the Ronald Reagan Building and International Trade Center on Monday, President Donald Trump outlined a foreign-policy manifesto rife with contradictions. “America will lead again,” he said, though he has moved to withdraw the United States from the world stage. “We do not seek to impose our way of life on anyone, but we will champion the values without apology,” he added, though which values were unclear.
